        <body>
            <div>
                <head>Comments</head>
                <p xml:id="CH1a0903-start">
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0903_CHANT_001-1a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#oesterg" modified="2020-05-29T18:09:41.409+09:00"/>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0903_CHANT_007-1a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#oesterg" modified="2020-05-20T17:43:30.087+09:00">The direct answer to this question
                        would be 吾以木言之 (“I shall explain this dictum by illustrating it with
                        features related to trees and wood”).</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0903_CHANT_007-1a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#oesterg" modified="2020-05-20T16:47:20.197+09:00">生 and 產 are treated as
                        synonyms.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0903_CHANT_007-1a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#oesterg" modified="2020-05-23T03:35:33.176+09:00">Excising 太山 following 群書治要 or read
                        太山 as 大山 (“big mountains”)</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0903_CHANT_007-1a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#oesterg" modified="2020-05-23T03:38:13.436+09:00">When a location is followed by 之下,
                        this probably has no meaning of “below” or the like. </seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0903_CHANT_007-1a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#oesterg" modified="2020-05-20T16:58:26.141+09:00">王利器 excises 於.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0903_CHANT_007-1a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#oesterg" modified="2020-05-20T17:04:57.345+09:00">Emending 精捍 to 精悍, following
                        王利器.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0903_CHANT_007-1a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#oesterg" modified="2020-05-20T17:16:13.307+09:00">Mei-kao Ku (254) claims that 博通
                        “refers to the annual rings of the trunk which becomes expanded when it is
                        sawn into two”; no attestation is given. The translation “elongated” is
                        tentative.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0903_CHANT_007-1a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="#oesterg" modified="2020-05-20T17:33:47.459+09:00">Insert 輭 for 軟 with 王利器.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0903_CHANT_007-1a.26" xml:lang="en" resp="#oesterg" modified="2020-05-26T18:51:10.705+09:00">王利器 emends 不 to 而, following 群書治要.
                        This makes it difficult to link with the preceding. I follow Yu Yue.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0903_CHANT_007-1a.29" xml:lang="en" resp="#oesterg" modified="2020-05-20T17:30:26.195+09:00">Instead of ��, insert 𡵻.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0903_CHANT_008-1a.1-h" xml:lang="en" resp="#oesterg" modified="2020-05-20T23:32:54.188+09:00"/>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0903_CHANT_008-2a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#oesterg" modified="2020-05-21T16:16:01.083+09:00">For 儴, read 懷.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0903_CHANT_008-2a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#oesterg" modified="2020-05-21T16:18:44.094+09:00">For 附, read 充.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0903_CHANT_008-3a.35" xml:lang="en" resp="#oesterg" modified="2020-05-21T17:43:58.299+09:00">For 刑, read 牢.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0903_CHANT_007-1a.30" xml:lang="en" resp="#oesterg" modified="2020-05-21T22:10:57.065+09:00">Cf. 頓仆.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0903_CHANT_007-1a.45" xml:lang="en" resp="#oesterg" modified="2020-05-21T22:26:28.265+09:00">Excise 尚.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0903_CHANT_007-1a.46" xml:lang="en" resp="#oesterg" modified="2020-05-21T22:27:21.85+09:00">𡻭𡻭</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0903_CHANT_007-1a.57" xml:lang="en" resp="#oesterg" modified="2020-05-21T23:20:44.787+09:00">Interpreting 斁 as 剫.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0903_CHANT_007-1a.74" xml:lang="en" resp="#oesterg" modified="2020-05-21T23:29:18.051+09:00">懸絕</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0903_CHANT_007-2a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#oesterg" modified="2020-05-22T19:36:24.187+09:00"/>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0903_CHANT_007-2a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#oesterg" modified="2020-05-22T19:36:28.21+09:00">For 用, read 容.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0903_CHANT_007-5a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#oesterg" modified="2020-05-22T20:09:57.126+09:00">translation doubtful</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0903_CHANT_007-5a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#oesterg" modified="2020-06-30T19:33:45.833+09:00">those who are close to the ruler,
                        acting as his ears and eyes, and who inform him about prospective
                        officials.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0903_CHANT_007-5a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#oesterg" modified="2020-06-30T19:40:25.591+09:00">translation doubtful</seg>
                </p>
            </div>
